$\mathbf{p} = [p_1, p_2, \dots, p_n]^T$ from observed measurements
$\mathbf{m} = [m_1, m_2, \dots, m_k]^T$:

\begin{equation}
\mathbf{m} = f(\mathbf{p}) + \boldsymbol{\epsilon}
\label{eq:general_inverse}
\end{equation}

where $f(\cdot)$ represents the forward model and $\boldsymbol{\epsilon}$ denotes
measurement noise.

