\label{subsec:hb_application}

The Herschel-Bulkley model captures non-Newtonian fluid behavior with yield stress:

\begin{equation}
\tau(\dot{\gamma}) = \tau_y + K \dot{\gamma}^n
\label{eq:herschel_bulkley}
\end{equation}

\subsubsection{Inverse Problem Solution}
Given experimental data $(\dot{\gamma}_i, \tau_i)$, we solve for $\mathbf{p} = [\tau_y, K, n]^T$:

